<subSubSection id="C33B6528FFDC4459FCBAFF01FCC30BB2" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="370" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9E36A3FFDC4458FCBAFF01FD5F0E70" blockId="2.[839,1482,194,441]" lastBlockId="2.[158,801,545,632]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FCBAFF01FC670CD1" bold="true" box="[839,957,194,217]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Among loricariines 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FB65FF01FAD00CD1" box="[1176,1290,194,217]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FB65FF01FAD00CD1" box="[1176,1290,194,217]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Ixinandria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FCBAFF21FC030CF1" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" box="[839,985,226,249]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rineloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FCBAFF21FC030CF1" box="[839,985,226,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Rineloricaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished from most genera by the total lack of abdominal plates, including the preanal plate. 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FCBAFEE1FC700D31" box="[839,938,290,313]" class="Ostracoda" family="Entocytheridae" genus="Hartiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FCBAFEE1FC700D31" box="[839,938,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Hartiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a few species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FB66FEE1FB310D31" box="[1179,1259,290,313]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Harttia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FB66FEE1FB310D31" box="[1179,1259,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Harttia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also have the abdomen completely devoid of plates, and can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FC7FFEA1FC2E0D71" box="[898,1012,354,377]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FC7FFEA1FC2E0D71" box="[898,1012,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Ixinandria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having 12 branched caudal-fin rays (vs. 
<quantity id="4CD99B46FFDC4458FCBAFE41FC5A0D91" box="[839,896,386,409]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FC74FE41FBDE0D91" box="[905,1028,386,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FC74FE41FC260D91" box="[905,1020,386,409]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ixinandria</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
and by the absence of postorbital notch, which is present in 
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FBE0FE61FB4C0DB1" box="[1053,1174,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FBE0FE61FB490DB1" box="[1053,1171,418,441]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ixinandria</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FAEBFE61FA180DB1" authorityName="Isbruecker" authorityYear="1979" box="[1302,1474,418,441]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Crossoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FAEBFE61FA180DB1" box="[1302,1474,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Crossoloricaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FF63FDE2FE3C0E30" authority="Isbrucker &amp; Nijssen" authorityName="Isbrucker &amp; Nijssen" box="[158,486,545,568]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FF63FDE2FED70E30" box="[158,269,545,568]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Ixinandria</emphasis>
Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB04B52FFDC4458FDFAFDE2FD0B0E30" author="Isbrucker, I. J" box="[519,721,545,568]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" pagination="86 - 116" refId="ref9917" refString="Isbrucker, I. J. H. 1979. Descriptions preliminaires de nouveaux taxa de la famille des Loricariidae. Revue Francaise d'Aquariologie, 5: 86 - 116." type="journal article" year="1979">Isbrücker, 1979: 87</bibRefCitation>
and 91, figs. 1-4. 
<typeStatus id="549A8801FFDC4458FEDBFD82FE810E50" box="[294,347,577,600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FE44FD82FCC70E50" authority="Regan, 1906" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1906" box="[441,797,577,600]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Himanthaliaceae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="steinbachi">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FE44FD82FD4B0E50" box="[441,657,577,600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Loricaria steinbachi</emphasis>
Regan, 1906
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation. Gender: feminine.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5E662BFFDC4458FF63F8E1FE750BB1" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" startId="2.[158,197,1826,1849]" targetBox="[168,782,693,1802]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8B9E36A3FFDC4458FF63F8E1FE750BB1" blockId="2.[158,801,1826,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FF63F8E1FF3E0B31" bold="true" box="[158,228,1826,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Fig. 1.</emphasis>
Plots of factor scores of principal component analysis of four populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDC4458FE4EF881FD6A0B51" baseAuthorityName="Regan" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[435,688,1858,1881]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steinbachi">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FE4EF881FD6A0B51" box="[435,688,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Ixinandria steinbachi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Dot, río Juramento basin; Square, southern upper río Bermejo basin; triangle, northern upper río Bermejo basin; and Star, río Pilcomayo. L = lectotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF5E662BFFDC4458FCBAF8A1FA5E0BB1" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" startId="2.[839,878,1890,1913]" targetBox="[870,1463,482,1865]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8B9E36A3FFDC4458FCBAF8A1FA5E0BB1" blockId="2.[839,1481,1890,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDC4458FCBAF8A1FC500B71" bold="true" box="[839,906,1890,1913]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
Strict consensus of the 26 best trees from the maximum parsimony analysis. Tree length: 151. Numbers above branches are values from 1000 bootstrap replications.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF5E662BFFDD4459FCC2FC1CFBBB087E" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" startId="3.[831,870,991,1014]" targetBox="[835,1470,195,973]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8B9E36A3FFDD4459FCC2FC1CFBBB087E" blockId="3.[831,1475,991,1142]" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FCC2FC1CFC5F0FFE" bold="true" box="[831,901,991,1014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Fig. 4.</emphasis>
Minimum spanning network of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FB26FC1CFA180FFE" baseAuthorityName="Regan" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1243,1474,991,1014]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steinbachi">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FB26FC1CFA180FFE" box="[1243,1474,991,1014]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Ixinandria steinbachi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
haplotypes. Distances correlate to the number of mutations in the sequence as marked by open dots. Circle size corresponds to frequency of haplotypes. White: Juramento, black: Bermejo 1, grey: Bermejo 2.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9E36A3FFDD4459FCC2FB67FAC20953" blockId="3.[831,1474,1188,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">
has wide and almost symmetrical tooth cusps, and up to 18 teeth in each premaxilla (
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FBB6FB07FBBB08D3" box="[1099,1121,1220,1243]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">vs</emphasis>
. premaxilla with up to 13 narrow and clearly asymmetrical teeth in other loricariines, except 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FCC2FAC7FBB10913" authorityName="Reis &amp; Cardoso" authorityYear="2001" box="[831,1131,1284,1307]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rineloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aequalicuspis">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FCC2FAC7FBB10913" box="[831,1131,1284,1307]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Rineloricaria aequalicuspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has up to 15 narrow teeth with nearly symmetrical cusps, and some hartiini, which also have many asymmetrical premaxillary teeth).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5E662BFFDD4459FF6AF996FE500AA4" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" startId="3.[151,191,1621,1644]" targetBox="[184,772,188,1598]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8B9E36A3FFDD4459FF6AF996FE500AA4" blockId="3.[151,794,1621,1708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FF6AF996FF390A64" bold="true" box="[151,227,1621,1644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Fig. 3.</emphasis>
Best tree from maximum likelihood analysis. –ln L=1643.94356. Numbers above branches are values from 1000 bootstrap replications.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9E36A3FFDD4459FF6AF920FCC30BB2" blockId="3.[151,794,1763,1978]" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FF6AF920FEE80AF2" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1944" box="[151,306,1763,1786]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Spatuloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FF6AF920FEE80AF2" box="[151,306,1763,1786]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Spatuloricaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FE94F920FE150AF2" box="[361,463,1763,1786]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Himanthaliaceae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FE94F920FE150AF2" box="[361,463,1763,1786]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Loricaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sometimes lack a preanal plate, but small abdominal plates are present. Some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FF6AF8E0FEF30B32" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,297,1827,1850]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rineloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FF6AF8E0FEF30B32" box="[151,297,1827,1850]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Rineloricaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a naked abdomen, but a preanal plate is always present, except in 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FE49F880FDE70B52" authorityName="Ghazzi" authorityYear="2008" box="[436,573,1859,1882]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rineloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="setepovos">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FE49F880FDE70B52" box="[436,573,1859,1882]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">R. setepovos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species, however, has a caudal-fin filament and 3-4 premaxillary teeth. 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FF6AF840FED30B92" box="[151,265,1923,1946]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FF6AF840FED30B92" box="[151,265,1923,1946]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Ixinandria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be distinguished from other loricariines by the shape and number of premaxillary teeth. 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D20FFDD4459FD5AF860FCC30BB2" box="[679,793,1955,1978]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ixinandria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955EAB1FFDD4459FD5AF860FCC30BB2" box="[679,793,1955,1978]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="370">Ixinandria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
